Communicated by:
ProMED

[The above media reports fill in some of the blanks raised in yesterday's post (see Poliomyelitis update (09): Israel (JM) VDPV, MOH, RFI 20220307.8701864). The population involved is the ultra-Orthodox community; a section of the population that has had suboptimal vaccination coverages through the years and has consequently had outbreaks of measles as a result of this. Preliminary results of epidemiologic investigation identified 30 known contacts at risk, but the prudent action taken by the public health sector to increase environmental sampling country-wide in order to cast a wide net and not miss the introduction to communities outside of Jerusalem.

We are still awaiting the results of genomic studies on the isolated virus.

A map of Israel can be found at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/israel_map.htm. Israel is a very small country geographically, and all points can be reached as a day trip from Jerusalem. - Mod.MPP

